  • Suitable for Space Up to 15m² - The Hangsun DL12 dehumidifier is able to collect 12L of moisture per day and adjust humidity from 30% to 80%. Once target humidity is reached, the unit will turn off to conserve energy. Perfect for use in home, basements, office, bathrooms, attics, garages, crawlspace or any large rooms up to 15m².
  • Intelligent Humidity Sensor with Indicator Lights - The automatic humidity sensor allows you to track room humidity, LED control panel will display the current humidity level. And the smart humidity colored indicator lights keeps you aware of the humidity around you. Blue: room humidity less than 45%; Green: room humidity is an optimum 45-65%; Red: room humidity is greater than 65%.
  • Advanced 3 Modes and 2 Speeds - The dehumidifier features 3 operating modes including AUTO/CONTINUOUS/SLEEP. Continuously drying mode is ideal for drying clothes or keeping your basement dry. Sleep mode with sound levels of less than 38dB allows you to work, read or sleep undisturbed. Two different fan speeds will meet the various dehumidification needs of anyone by switching freely. The built-in auto defrost function prevents the collected water from being frozen and doing harm to the machine.
  • 2 Ways for Your Draining Choices - Equipped with a large detachable 2L water tank. When the water tank is full, this smart dehumidifier will automatically shut down, and the full water indicator will light up to prevent water overflow. No time to empty it? A drain hose outlet for continuous draining which comes with a 41.35 inch long drain hose that you don't need to empty the water tank anytime.
  • Designed with Effortless Use in Mind – The timer allows you to schedule the dehumidifier to turn on or off over a 24-hour window. The filter of dehumidifier is removable and easy to clean. It even comes with 360° rotatable wheels and a safe child lock that makes it easy to move the dehumidifier anywhere you want without any safety concerns.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
5 out of 5 stars
Great bit of kit.
I bought this to try to help dry my clothes quicker and so far I'm very impressed. On this airer it normally takes 2/3 days for the clothes to be fully dry (with no heating on as it's early October and I refuse to put my heating on this early). They were dry overnight! I initially set it to continous drying but found it wasn't bringing the humidity down. I switched to automatic at a humidity setting of 50 and that seems to work. I also have a damp bathroom so I've moved it upstairs ( the humidity was 83 when I turned the machine on ). The humidity came down very quickly still on auto mode. It's located on the landing so I've turned the mode to sleep and I can't really hear it. I'm really hoping as it get's colder that it will continue to dry my clothes and help with damp with limited heating on, only time will tell but so far, I'm very impressed. Jonny
5.0 out of 5 stars Exceeds expectations
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 13 August 2023
Verified Purchase
I wanted a dehumidifier to help keep on top of high humidity levels at home (dormer bungalow). It's not uncommon for humidity to reach 80% on colder/wet days, especially over the winter months.

I wanted a dehumidifier that had a timer, display of humidity level and an automatic cut off once the desired humidity was achieved.

On arrival I was initially quite disappointed with the size as it was a fair bit smaller than I expected. This is entirely my fault as I gauged the size from images rather than reading the actual dimensions.

I wasn't hopeful but plugged it in and hoped for the best. The unit had a little red colour display to show the humidity level was high. After an hour of use I returned to find that the unit had surpassed surpassed expectations and had gathered approximate 2 litres of water! The humidity percentage had dropped 10% within that hour.

I emptied the container and left the unit running. Over the cause of about 6 hours use I was averaging approximately a little less than a litre an hour which was superb as I was watching the humidity level drop in real time.

The unit requires 30cm clearance around it so please be mindful of this when buying.

It's a fairly heavy and robust unit but has 4 wheels which means it's very easy to manoeuvre around the home.

It comes with:
*Green (good humidity level) or Red (bad humidity level) led light
* current humidity percentage display
* Timer
* Fan speed
* varies modes such as automatic, constant etc.
* automatic tank shut off or continous use via drain off hose

Please note that some reviews say the buttons don't work however this isn't 100% true. Not all functions are compatible with the various modes and settings.

I am very happy with the purchase, I paid a very fair price at sale coat and am happy to recommend the unit.
